stylometry: Sensitiviy Analysis is a tool that allows us to see the changes in one variable such as profit , if another variable such as fixed costs changes.  It is important because it allows us to see the changes and helps us determine if we need to minimize one of the variables in order to maximize our profit.  Sometimes you might not be able to see if this will happen unless you do a sensitivity analysis.  Solvertable is a tool that allows us to put the different variables into the links and put the constraints in along with other types of information required in our model. It is very similar to solver, but has different parts you are able to put into the table in which to solve.
